<paper id="1588263062"><title>Usage Scenarios and Goals for Ontology Definition Metamodel</title><year>2004</year><authors><author org="AT&amp;T Government Solutions, Inc," id="2138010900">Lewis Hart</author><author org="AT&amp;T Government Solutions, Inc," id="2128519237">Patrick Emery</author><author org="the University of Queensland" id="700536811">Robert M. Colomb</author><author org="DSTC PTY LTD" id="2287115224">Kerry Raymond</author><author org="IBM Silicon Valley Labs#TAB#" id="2496047814">Dan Chang</author><author org="IBM, Watson Research Center" id="2688572038">Yiming Ye</author><author org="Sandpiper Software, Inc" id="2149085524">Elisa F. Kendall</author><author org="Sandpiper Software, Inc" id="2326832637">Mark Dutra</author></authors><n_citation>17</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1584585813</reference></references><venue id="1128202388" type="C">Web Information Systems Engineering</venue><doi>10.1007/978-3-540-30480-7_62</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.48495">Information system</keyword><keyword weight="0.67428">Ontology (information science)</keyword><keyword weight="0.55509">Ontology</keyword><keyword weight="0.43476">Data mining</keyword><keyword weight="0.4438">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.81971">Ontology Definition MetaModel</keyword><keyword weight="0.44362">Database</keyword><keyword weight="0.5172">Metamodeling</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>This paper contains a taxonomy of the uses of ontologies, intended as motivation for the Ontology Definition Metamodel development effort by the Object Management Group. It describes several usage scenarios for ontologies and proposes example applications for use in these scenarios. Many of the scenarios and applications are based on efforts currently underway in industry and academia. The scenarios descriptions are followed by goals for the Ontology Definition Metamodel.</abstract></paper>